    "project_template_level_name": "CSA U2L8-Compound PBT_2025",
    "teacher_markdown": "After adding the first code segment, students will see the following printed to the console:\r\n\r\n```\r\nResult: 0\r\nResult + number: 2\r\nResult * number: 4\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is because on **Line 9**, the value assigned to `number` (`2`) is added to `result`. After **Line 9**, the value of `result` is `2`.\r\n\r\nWhen `result` is multiplied by the value assigned to `number` (`2`), the result is `2 * 2`, so `4` is assigned to `result`.\r\n\r\nAfter adding the second code segment, students will see the following printed to the console:\r\n\r\n```\r\nResult: 0\r\nResult + number: 2\r\nResult * number: 4\r\nResult - number: 2\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe value assigned to `result` is updated to the current value of `result` (`4`) minus the value assigned to `number` (`2`). The result is `2`, which is assigned to `result`.\r\n\r\nAfter adding the third code segment, students will see the following printed to the console:\r\n\r\n```\r\nResult: 0\r\nResult + number: 2\r\nResult * number: 4\r\nResult - number: 2\r\nResult / number: 1\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe value assigned to `result` is updated to the current value of `result` (`2`) divided by the value assigned to `number` (`2`). The result is `1`, which is assigned to `result`.",
